{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idc043e8cd-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18013"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"18013"},"text":"§ 18013.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Annual report on self-insured plans","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Not later than 1 year after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2010-03-23"},"text":"March 23, 2010","children":[],"tail":", and annually thereafter, the Secretary of Labor shall prepare an aggregate annual report, using data collected from the Annual Return/Report of Employee Benefit Plan (Department of Labor Form 5500), that shall include general information on self-insured group health plans (including plan type, number of participants, benefits offered, funding arrangements, and benefit arrangements) as well as data from the financial filings of self-insured employers (including information on assets, liabilities, contributions, investments, and expenses). The Secretary shall submit such reports to the appropriate committees of Congress."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idc043e8ce-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/148/tI/s1253"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–148, title I, § 1253","children":[],"tail":", as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/148/tX/s10103/f/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–148, title X, § 10103(f)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2010-03-23"},"text":"Mar. 23, 2010","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/124/895"},"text":"124 Stat. 895","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idc043e8cf-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idc043e8d0-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213